This confirms the root cause with high confidence.

Configuration mismatch

Your SriovNetwork objects are configured to use resources that do not exist.

You have:

bscf-bh0u-3-nad
spec:
  resourceName: pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

and

bscf-bh0u-3-1-nad
spec:
  resourceName: pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3_1

But your node advertises only:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_1
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2_1

There is no:

openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3
openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3_1

Likewise, your SriovNetworkNodePolicy objects exist only for:

policy-ens1f0-bh0u
policy-ens3f3-bh0u-1
policy-ens4f0-bh0u-2
policy-ens6f0-bh0u-2-1

There are no policies that create:

pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3_1


Therefore the SR-IOV device plugin cannot advertise those resources, and the scheduler reports:

Insufficient openshift.io/pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

Why this happened

Your Helm chart created:

SriovNetwork for bh0u-3

SriovNetwork for bh0u-3-1


but did not create the corresponding SriovNetworkNodePolicy objects.

This is why the NADs exist but the resources are unavailable.

Verify whether your server actually has those NICs

Run:

oc get sriovnetworknodestate ocp-sno.lab10.ocp.lan \
-n openshift-sriov-network-operator -o yaml | grep -A10 "interfaces:"

or, more specifically:

oc get sriovnetworknodestate ocp-sno.lab10.ocp.lan \
-n openshift-sriov-network-operator -o yaml | grep "name:"

You should see interface names such as:

ens1f0
ens3f3
ens4f0
ens6f0

If there are no additional interfaces (for example ens7f0 or similar), then bh0u_3 and bh0u_3_1 are invalid for this server.

The fix depends on your hardware

Case 1: The server has only 4 PFs (most likely)

Your Helm values are incorrect. The deployment should use the existing resources:

pci_sriov_net_bh0u

pci_sriov_net_bh0u_1

pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2

pci_sriov_net_bh0u_2_1


instead of bh0u_3 and bh0u_3_1.

Case 2: The server should have additional PFs

Then you must create matching SriovNetworkNodePolicy objects for:

pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3

pci_sriov_net_bh0u_3_1


so the device plugin advertises those resources.


